A specialized web-based productivity tool designed for high-focus scientific environments. This application combines a precision countdown timer with a persistent lab checklist to streamline experimental workflows.


ğŸ§ª Overview
The Lab Timer is a minimalist, single-file web application that leverages a "Scientific Blue" aesthetic to provide a professional and calm workspace for students and researchers. It uses state-aware logic to transition through different stages of a research "Analysis" session.





ğŸ§¬ Key Features
ğŸ“¡ State-Aware Interface
The application interface reflects the current progress of the experiment through dynamic emoji states and CSS animations:



Ready State (ğŸ§ª): The default idle state where the system is prepared for a new session.



Analyzing State (ğŸ”¬): Activated during the 15-minute countdown, featuring a pulsing animation to simulate active work.



Complete State (âœ…): Triggered once the timer reaches zero, accompanied by a notification chime.


ğŸ“ Integrated Lab Checklist
To ensure no steps are missed during a focus block, the app includes a persistent checklist:


Dynamic Task Entry: Quickly add experimental steps via the input field.


LocalStorage Persistence: Tasks are saved in the browser's local storage, ensuring data remains intact even after a page refresh.


Interactive Management: Users can toggle strike-throughs for completed tasks or clear the entire list with a single click.

â±ï¸ Precision Timer Logic

Default Duration: Pre-set to 15 minutes, optimized for standard laboratory intervals.


Comprehensive Controls: Includes Start, Pause, and Reset functionalities to manage unexpected interruptions during analysis.



Notification System: Features an audible alert to signify the completion of the countdown.

ğŸ¨ Design Aesthetic
The application follows a "Scientific Blue" color palette, utilizing soft pastel blues and a subtle radial grid background to mimic laboratory documentation. It is designed with a responsive "Case Study Card" layout, making it suitable for integration into professional portfolios.



